From: Raspberry Pi Ltd <kernel@raspberrypi.com>
Date: Mon, 10 Mar 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] net: phy: broadcom: disable AutogrEEEn mode on BCM54xx

Two commits from rpi-6.18.y kernel combined (raspberrypi/linux PR #7270):

1. net: phy: broadcom: fix BCM54213PE per-PHY init never called
   (commit f7576c7831a1)

   BCM54213PE (PHY_ID = 0x600d84a2) and BCM54210E share the same model
   ID when masked by PHY_ID_MATCH_MODEL_MASK (0xfffffff0).  As a result,
   the switch/case dispatch in bcm54xx_config_init() blindly ran
   bcm54210e_config_init() for BCM54213PE PHYs and bcm54213pe_config_init()
   was dead code.  Fix by checking phydev->drv->phy_id (the exact driver
   ID, set from the per-PHY match table) inside the BCM54210E case to
   dispatch to bcm54213pe_config_init() when appropriate.

2. net: phy: broadcom: disable AutogrEEEn mode on BCM54xx
   (commit 89d02e4dc84a)

   BCM54xx PHYs default to AutogrEEEn mode (MII_BUF_CNTL_0 bit 0), which
   manages EEE Low Power Idle autonomously without forwarding LPI signaling
   to the MAC.  The Cadence macb/GEM driver (used on RP1) does not have
   built-in EEE/LPI awareness in older kernels; even after adding it
   the MAC must be able to observe RGMII RX LPI to participate in the
   standard IEEE 802.3az negotiation.  AutogrEEEn intercepts LPI before it
   reaches the MAC → the MAC sees dropped packets rather than LPI idle.

   Fix by clearing MII_BUF_CNTL_0[0] in bcm54xx_config_init() to disable
   AutogrEEEn and switch the PHY to Native EEE mode, where LPI signaling
   is forwarded through the RGMII interface as expected by 802.3az.

   Root cause of silent packet loss on Raspberry Pi CM5 (BCM54213PE +
   RP1 macb/GEM): the PHY silently entered LPI while the MAC continued
   transmitting, dropping frames without any error counters or logs.

Link: https://github.com/siderolabs/sbc-raspberrypi/issues/82
Link: https://github.com/raspberrypi/linux/commit/f7576c7831a1
Link: https://github.com/raspberrypi/linux/commit/89d02e4dc84a
Signed-off-by: Raspberry Pi Ltd <kernel@raspberrypi.com>
---
 drivers/net/phy/broadcom.c | 24 ++++++++++++++++++------
 include/linux/brcmphy.h    |  3 +++
 2 files changed, 21 insertions(+), 6 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/net/phy/broadcom.c b/drivers/net/phy/broadcom.c
--- a/drivers/net/phy/broadcom.c
+++ b/drivers/net/phy/broadcom.c
@@ -490,6 +490,15 @@ static int bcm54xx_config_init(struct phy_device *phydev)
 	if (of_property_read_bool(np, "brcm,powerdown-enable"))
 		phydev->dev_flags |= PHY_BRCM_AUTO_PWRDWN_ENABLE;
 
+	/* Disable AutogrEEEn and switch to Native EEE mode so the MAC
+	 * can control LPI signaling and observe RX LPI on the RGMII
+	 * interface.
+	 */
+	err = bcm_phy_modify_exp(phydev, BCM54XX_TOP_MISC_MII_BUF_CNTL0,
+				 BCM54XX_MII_BUF_CNTL0_AUTOGREEEN_EN, 0);
+	if (err)
+		return err;
+
 	bcm54xx_adjust_rxrefclk(phydev);
 
 	switch (phydev->drv->phy_id & PHY_ID_MATCH_MODEL_MASK) {
@@ -498,14 +507,17 @@ static int bcm54xx_config_init(struct phy_device *phydev)
 		break;
 	case PHY_ID_BCM54210E:
-		err = bcm54210e_config_init(phydev);
+		/* BCM54213PE shares the same model ID as BCM54210E; use the
+		 * exact driver ID to dispatch to the right per-PHY init.
+		 */
+		if (phydev->drv->phy_id == PHY_ID_BCM54213PE)
+			err = bcm54213pe_config_init(phydev);
+		else
+			err = bcm54210e_config_init(phydev);
 		break;
 	case PHY_ID_BCM54612E:
 		err = bcm54612e_config_init(phydev);
 		break;
-	case PHY_ID_BCM54213PE:
-		err = bcm54213pe_config_init(phydev);
-		break;
 	case PHY_ID_BCM54616S:
 		err = bcm54616s_config_init(phydev);
 		break;

diff --git a/include/linux/brcmphy.h b/include/linux/brcmphy.h
--- a/include/linux/brcmphy.h
+++ b/include/linux/brcmphy.h
@@ -267,6 +267,9 @@
 #define BCM54XX_TOP_MISC_IDDQ_SD		(1 << 2)
 #define BCM54XX_TOP_MISC_IDDQ_SR		(1 << 3)
 
+#define BCM54XX_TOP_MISC_MII_BUF_CNTL0		(MII_BCM54XX_EXP_SEL_TOP + 0x00)
+#define  BCM54XX_MII_BUF_CNTL0_AUTOGREEEN_EN	BIT(0)
+
 #define BCM54XX_TOP_MISC_LED_CTL		(MII_BCM54XX_EXP_SEL_TOP + 0x0C)
 #define  BCM54XX_LED4_SEL_INTR			BIT(1)
 
